There are a few strange style choices (? errors) in this.



Tests covering SCP-002-PT, SCP-002—A or SCP-002-PT-B
附加记录：    

Missing a PT here?

Not sure why 'teen' and 'offset' are italicised. I don't like the double footnotes - it's unwieldy and a lot of the footnotes could be folded into the body of the text. Footnote 7 is oddly phrased with the brackets, it conflates SSRIs with behavioural therapy as phrased and I don't know what TCD is.



about 50 e 85kg
附加记录：    

This is a holdover from Portuguese, right?

I know plenty of people use commas as decimal separators but part of me feels like English-language articles should use periods. I'll leave that up to translators, though.

Anyway, with that out of the way, I didn't like this starting out, but it got better later (the reverse is more common). It starts out as a thing that makes you crazy which comes off a bit edgy, and I could stand to see less of that. However, the hallucinations had a nice feel of strangeness with comprehension/logic just out of reach, and the article toed the edgy line a bit but pulled it off with some great cheery-yet-wrong feeling. +1







